BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ghyjjajVjMM5h9GfBO-Dj
SUMMARY:SAM Body + Mind: Activity Days
DTSTAMP:20260318T063032Z
DTSTART:20260321T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Experience a full spectrum of grounding\, creative\, and wellne
	ss-focused practices with SAM Body \\+ Mind: Activity Days. Designed to re
	juvenate both inner and outer worlds\, each session offers a mix of mindfu
	l movement\, quiet reflection\, hands-on creativity\, and holistic care. P
	articipate in gentle Qigong to awaken your energy\, enjoy replenishing mom
	ents with acupuncture\, or settle into the calm of silent reading in a pea
	ceful shared space. Explore your artistic side with natural dye and art-ma
	king workshops that nourish connections to yourself and the natural world.
	 Come for one activity or stay for the full experience-each offering invit
	es you to slow down\, reconnect\, and care for your body and mind. 8:30 am
	 | Doors open 9-10 am | Tai Chi/Qigong With Sensei Jody Garcia 10 am-1 pm 
	| Workshops Art workshop with NW Expressive and Creative Arts Institute Na
	tural dyes workshop with Earth Corps Acupuncture with Dr. Yanzi Jiang\, Dr
	. Milo Jackson\, and Dr. Nikeeta Shah noon-2 pm | Musical performance Ambi
	ent Vinyl DJ set performed by DJ Raica 1-2 pm | Silent reading With West S
	eattle Book Club Food and drinks Food and beverages will be available for 
	purchase from Shooby Doo Catering in the PACCAR Pavilion. Presenting Spons
	or\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/sam-body-mind-activity
	-days/17592413/2026-03-21T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/sam-body-mind-activity-da
	ys/17592413/2026-03-21T00
LOCATION:Olympic Sculpture Park\, 2901 Western Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:WReZHJNfRfJZljcBu0bE2
SUMMARY:Alaska Cruise & Travel Show
DTSTAMP:20260318T063032Z
DTSTART:20260321T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Event Overview Join us in Seattle for the Alaska Cruise & Trave
	l Show and begin planning your voyage to one of the world's most extraordi
	nary destinations. This immersive event brings together travel inspiration
	\, cultural experiences\, and exclusive cruise offers all in one place. Ex
	perience live music and theater presentations that celebrate Alaska's land
	scapes and heritage. Participate in hands-on activities including gold pan
	ning and axe throwing and meet with cruise specialists to explore itinerar
	ies and take advantage of limited-time booking offers. Attendees may enter
	 for the chance to win one Alaska cruise for two and one of six $500 Holla
	nd America Line gift cards. Admission is free. Reserve your place at www.a
	laskatravelshow.com.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/alas
	ka-cruise-travel-show/18224461/2026-03-21T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Cul
	ture
